will my new kitten get along with my year old cat i just got a new month old kitten and my older cat is years old they havnt really had a major fight but my older cat hits the kitten when it comes near him because my older cat has a very shy and scared temprement will it stop him and my kitten getting along or becoming friends or is it normal for them to act that way it is perfectly normal for your cat to react that way to the kitten cats are very territorial animals and your older cat is trying to set the 'pecking order' in the house remember to give equal attention to both cats and eventually your cat and kitten will work things out on their own keep in mind though they may become best of friends or they may just learn to tolerate each other Cat Socialization Kitten Azumanga Daioh El Goonish Shive Marc Antony and Pussyfoot The Aristocats Feral cat Ferret Big Brother UK series 5 Cats (musical) Ranma __ characters Feral Social rule Manx (cat) Puma Tokyo Mew Mew Animal communication B3ta Louis Wain Siamese (cat) Garfield Cuteness Badly Drawn Kitties Atomic Kitten Joy Division (band) Bast (goddess) Lie Mickey Mouse Doug Bobcat Pitaten Phoebe Buffay's songs Minor characters in Teen Titans (animated series) The Beatles bootlegs Shaggy dog story Lunar: The Silver Star Galaxy Angel Xiaolin Showdown Lady and the Tramp The Cat in the Hat Elektra (comics) Rabbit Domestic rabbit Puss in Boots Cat's Cradle Catgirl Abu Dhabi Garfield and Friends Scottish Gaelic language Gerund Ralston Purina Company Lion Minor characters in Sonic the Hedgehog Treecat Pet skunk Studio Ironcat Internet phenomenon Softball Pet store Cockfight Kim Possible Leopard Cat Claude Cat Philosophy of language Chinese calendar Serval W.I.T.C.H. Catwoman Characters in the Smurfs Gunsmith Cats Cheetah Chuck Jones Sabrina: The Animated Series Minor Harry Potter Beasts Love Hina main characters Spot the Dog Egyptian Mau Fruits Basket RuneScape quests Spanish pronouns Chromosome Shen Gong Wu Koko (gorilla) Phant